systemctl edit sshd

## This opens a drop-in override file, not the main service file (/etc/systemd/system/sshd.service.d/override.conf)

In the file you will see the following comment:

### Lines below this comment will be discarded ###

## Add what you want to override above that line

Example: add the following…

[Service]
Restart=on-failure
RestartSec=5s

Save the file
Apply the change

systemctl daemon-reexec
systemctl restart sshd

Verify

systemctl show sshd | grep Restart
